brief_title: Exercise Training and Plasma Lipoproteins in Man
brief_summary: To determine the effects in moderately obese subjects of weight loss by combined dieting and exercise training on risk factors for coronary artery disease including lipoprotein lipids, apoproteins and blood pressure.
condition: Cardiovascular Diseases Coronary Disease Heart Diseases Hypertension Myocardial Ischemia Obesity
eligibility_criteria: Men and women, ages 25-49. Subjects were overweight with blood pressure less than 160/95 mm Hg and total cholesterol less than 260 mm/dl.
